HEADWORD: Protoplasmic
<hw>Pro`to*plas"mic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to the first formation of living bodies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to protoplasm;
consisting of, or resembling, protoplasm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protoplast</ent>⟦br⟧
